attributes.additional_details:
According to the Government website “In the UK, 1 in 5 people have a disability” 
We believe that all house sale Home/Homebuyers Reports in the UK should, to enable potential buyers the full information for their needs, include:
Door opening widths;
Step height, depths and number;
Ramp widths and degree of angle, if applicable.
This should be mandatory to give disabled people the information they require to decide whether a house is accessible for them.
